ATS-Friendly
The label indicates that the template has a machine-readable format consisting of a one-column layout, no background colours, chronological content flow, common headings, clear typography hierarchy, non-creative fonts, and proper spacing. As a result, your CV using such a template has better odds of being parsed correctly by Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS), which most large companies utilise to streamline the recruiting process.

You can manage your preferences below and change or withdraw your consent via Privacy Settings at any time.

These cookies and storage items are necessary for the website to function properly and cannot be turned off. They enable core features such as security, session management, and payment processing. These first‑party cookies are set by Google Analytics 4 (GA4) to help us understand how visitors use our site. GA4 runs inside Google's EU Data Boundary: your full IP address never leaves the EU and is truncated before storage. We see only aggregated, anonymous statistics (e.g., which pages are popular, how long people stay). No cross‑site tracking and no additional advertising cookies or IDs are stored. We have signed Google's EU Data‑Processing Terms and use GA4's built‑in data‑retention and deletion tools to erase user‑level data on request. Learn more at Google's Privacy Policy.

If you also grant Marketing Cookies consent, GA4 reuses the same anonymous identifier to help Google Ads build audiences. GA4 itself sets no extra cookies; the only additional storage involved – the first‑party linker cookie "_gcl_aw" (plus "_gcl_ls" in localStorage) – is listed in the Marketing Cookies section below.
